nt as described below.\n\t\n\tImprovements: \n\t\nWe were not able to rebill overage on this one, which comes out to 470.45mt, or less than $2k USD at 50%. On this voyage it works in our favor as opposed to 50% overage after 145kmt.\n\t\nThe below clause was helpful to have as vessel was delayed just under 2 days for USCG COC and USCG Security inspection. This time will be rebilled to charterers.\n\t\nIf Owners fail;\n1. to obtain Customs clearance; and/or\n2. to obtain free pratique unless this is not customary prior\nto berthing; and/or\n3. to have on board all papers/certificates required to\nperform this Charter, either within the 6 hours after\nnotice of readiness originally tendered or when time would\notherwise normally commence under this Charter, then the\noriginal notice of readiness shall not be valid. A new\nnotice of readiness may only be tendered when Customs\nclearance and/or free pratique has been granted and/or all\npapers/certificates required are in order in accordance\nwith relevant authorities\u2019 requirements. Laytime or\ndemurrage, if on demurrage, would then commence in\naccordance with the terms of this Charter. All time, costs\nand expenses as a result of delays due to any of the\nforegoing shall be for Owners\u2019 account. Time waiting for\nitems (i), (ii) (iii) for customs and other port clearances\nfor Charterer\u0027s account, provided Owners have acted with\ndue diligence and in a timely manner."},{"modifiedDate":"2021-11-25T16:31:02.997","modifiedByFull":"Wright, Bryan","remark":"TC Increase $2k with est demurrage and less bunkers at disport"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-11-05T15:00:43.317","modifiedByFull":"Ngunza, Jose","remark":""}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}